<subSubSection id="CA07142BBFFCF573639C217D5C8F3D98" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" type="notes">
<paragraph id="923DA1BF1D71A7004D63AE7E7FDB9ABE" pageId="12" pageNumber="101">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CCD990CE89B6236C477D23575906444D" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="12" pageNumber="101">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="E121593C7C6BD35776CF59CB1FBA1AB3" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<bibRefCitation id="34012D89778FC143D2BA10CBEE1204D8" author="Saccardo, PA" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.80010" year="1882">Saccardo (1882)</bibRefCitation>
for two species, 
<taxonomicName id="0E672932C17CCF651F1F80653BBFB43C" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis spodiaea" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="spodiaea">Melanconis spodiaea</taxonomicName>
Tul. &amp; C. Tul. and 
<taxonomicName id="AAAB1BA5D5E40CE693C783F7AFCD0489" genus="M." lsidName="M. chrysostroma" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="chrysostroma">M. chrysostroma</taxonomicName>
(Fr.) Tul. &amp; C. Tul. The genus subsequently entered a long period of confusion with a broad concept of the melanconidaceous genera 
<taxonomicName id="47A1C4FB648934FDC4ADB6E21673D975" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconium</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0CD2FFD19F80EEE168FF33CA1DF58F22" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
Tul. &amp; C. Tul. (
<bibRefCitation id="407D3AEE075BAB570776A7BFCAD87937" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="599 - 617" title="Studies of certain species of Melanconis on Carpinus, Ostrya and Corylus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3754513" volume="29" year="1937">Wehmeyer 1937</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="842DBD46D77187F0C53C39CA1E19E61D" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="University of Michigan Studies, Scientiﬁc Series" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 161" title="A revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium and Titania." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3754513" volume="14" year="1941">1941</bibRefCitation>
; Barr 1987). 
<taxonomicName id="B13A15F4CA3E26995E900FE9B0DE185B" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
has 37 species epithets recorded in Index Fungorum (2018). 
<bibRefCitation id="0D1D3869987EF59BBFCB0133C2E46175" author="Voglmayr, H" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 44" title="Multigene phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Melanconiella (Diaporthales)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-012-0175-8" volume="57" year="2012">Voglmayr et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
revised the generic circumscriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="6C42E965FA19C6B0E70470A913219EE2" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
with 13 accepted species, excluded numerous species and confirmed that it is genetically distinct from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8905BDA74CD2B3E0D6D0CA4A2E6F9E40" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
based on morphology and multi-gene phylogeny (ITS, LSU, RPB2 and TEF1-α). 
<taxonomicName id="2A37838FFE589802EDC38B561B1DAD80" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
is characterised by forming circularly arranged perithecia immersed in the substrate with oblique or lateral ostioles convergent and erumpent through an ectostromatic disc with dark coloured or hyaline ascospores; acervuli with light-coloured central column, producing dark brown melanconium-like or hyaline discosporina-like conidia (not in the same species) (
<bibRefCitation id="120458874E20334C1585A5CE15A65E4A" author="Barr, ME" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia Memoir" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 232" title="The Diaporthales in North America with emphasis on Gnomonia and its segregates." volume="7" year="1978">Barr 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2770E9CCB561F166399BECD7C11AFCED" author="Voglmayr, H" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 44" title="Multigene phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Melanconiella (Diaporthales)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-012-0175-8" volume="57" year="2012">
<pageBreakToken id="A9CA5D156BD670B7F40CE955033F5D34" pageId="13" pageNumber="102" start="start">Voglmayr</pageBreakToken>
et al. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="DDE416DFDDAB133EC52069B3F92686C7" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="13" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
species were observed to be highly host-specific, as they were found to be confined to a single genus or sometimes even species within the host family 
<taxonomicName id="6EDFD31A121CA5CDDDF18B657205AFAC" family="Betulaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="13" pageNumber="102" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
from Europe and North America (
<bibRefCitation id="00B618BDD3C06825D94103C7CC94626E" author="Voglmayr, H" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 44" title="Multigene phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Melanconiella (Diaporthales)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-012-0175-8" volume="57" year="2012">Voglmayr et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
